CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 4, 1943, pg. 14, reads: "Elkdom on Parade! ... Thousands See Colorful Event ... Nation Represented. Tuesday afternoon, the Elks held their famous annual convention parade.  Up and down the hills of Pittsburgh marched the members of the Antlered Herd to the cheers and applause of thousands of spectators.  While not as long as parades in other years, it was still colorful and entertaining... 6. The Philadelphia delegation left everyone know they were present.  A big sign, 'Here Comes Philadelphia,' was carried by the brothers from the Quaker City... - Courier Photos by Harris, Sockwell and Olmstead."
TitMainTitle: Annual Elks parade, with men marching with banner inscribed "Here Comes Philadelphia," near Northside Elks Lodge No. 124, Wylie Avenue, Hill District
